Anytime I see multiple IAPs, I'm hesitant to make a purchase (especially if I have to buy the game, too). But, since Google increased the refund time limit, I feel safer testing apps. I'm glad I finally bought a license! The IAPs are onetime purchases and there are no consumables to buy. Anything unlocked is permanent (except, apparently, from all the reviews, their database was recently reset). The game is fun, though the flying is a bit simplified, but when fighting, this just may be a good thing. I didn't do the math, but the total to unlock all four IAPs is about $7 (USD, plus the $1 to buy a license). I'm going to play a bit before buying anything, but so far, I'm enjoying myself. I usually play RPGs, but occasionally like to branch out. With owning almost all RORTOS apps, I didn't think I'd like this one (I haven't liked any other flight game), but I'm glad I tried it as I really wanted to play against others (I don't usually play online games on my tablet). Without question, though a little expensive for Android, I'm going to keep it. Believe the other good reviews, it's all true! I don't say this often about Android games, but I'm impressed.
